    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The lake was formed by damming three natural spring‑fed ponds, creating an impoundment that now hosts popular fishing.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        13
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://dec.ny.gov/places/lime-lake"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "Anglers note that from June to September the lake experiences oxygen depletion below 20 feet, affecting fish behavior.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        19
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 1"
      ],
      "source": "https://dec.ny.gov/places/lime-lake"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "In the 1930s, Pulitzer‑winning sportswriter Jim Murray worked as a dishwasher at the historic Lime Lake Hotel.",
